---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import "../styles/home-modern.css";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Berrystock Solutions"
  description="Senior cloud engineering, identity, automation, and systems integration. Azure, AWS, Salesforce, and the full stack in between."
>
  <div class="page-wrap">

    <section class="hero">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="kicker reveal">Berrystock Solutions · London</div>

        <h1 class="h-display reveal">
          Complex infrastructure.<br />
          <span class="accent">Delivered clean.</span>
        </h1>

        <div class="actions reveal">
          <button class="btn btn-primary" type="button" data-modal-open>
            Get in Touch <span class="arr">›</span>
          </button>
          <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/services">See what we do</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <div class="statement-block reveal">
      <div class="container">
        <span class="statement-line">Your cloud grew fast. Access is a mess.</span>
        <span class="statement-line">The tools were bought. Nothing shipped.</span>
        <span class="statement-line"><span class="accent">That's exactly where we start.</span></span>
      </div>
    </div>

    <section class="section">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="section-inner reveal">
          <p class="kicker">What we do</p>
          <h2 class="section-title">Real outcomes. Across the full stack.</h2>
          <p class="section-lead">Not a generalist. Not an agency. A senior engineer who has done it — cloud spend cut, IAM cleaned up, platforms built from zero.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="service-grid reveal">
          <div class="service-card">
            <div class="service-icon">☁</div>
            <h3>Cloud platforms</h3>
            <p>Landing zones, IaC, governance, and secure networking on Azure and AWS.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="service-card">
            <div class="service-icon">⬡</div>
            <h3>Identity & access</h3>
            <p>JIT access, RBAC cleanup, conditional access, and IAM that actually works.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="service-card">
            <div class="service-icon">◈</div>
            <h3>FinOps & governance</h3>
            <p>Cost tagging, budget controls, and policy guardrails that stop surprise bills.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="service-card">
            <div class="service-icon">⚙</div>
            <h3>Automation & systems</h3>
            <p>Salesforce, HubSpot, Make, and custom pipelines, integrated and running.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="service-card" style="grid-column: span 4; border-top: 1px solid var(--border-d);">
            <div class="service-icon">◎</div>
            <h3>AI & automation agents</h3>
            <p>Agents and pipelines built with the controls and audit trails that production actually requires.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="marquee-wrap">
          <div class="marquee-track">
            <span class="marquee-item">Azure landing zones</span>
            <span class="marquee-item">IAM & RBAC</span>
            <span class="marquee-item">FinOps & cost control</span>
            <span class="marquee-item">Terraform & Bicep</span>
            <span class="marquee-item">AWS workloads</span>
            <span class="marquee-item">Salesforce & HubSpot</span>
            <span class="marquee-item">On-prem migration</span>
            <span class="marquee-item">JIT access</span>
            <span class="marquee-item">Make / n8n / Zapier</span>
            <span class="marquee-item">Azure landing zones</span>
            <span class="marquee-item">IAM & RBAC</span>
            <span class="marquee-item">FinOps & cost control</span>
            <span class="marquee-item">Terraform & Bicep</span>
            <span class="marquee-item">AWS workloads</span>
            <span class="marquee-item">Salesforce & HubSpot</span>
            <span class="marquee-item">On-prem migration</span>
            <span class="marquee-item">JIT access</span>
            <span class="marquee-item">Make / n8n / Zapier</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="section-inner reveal">
          <p class="kicker">How it works</p>
          <h2 class="section-title">No account managers. No handoffs.</h2>
          <p class="section-lead">You talk to the engineer. The engineer does the work. You get something you can run.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="step-grid">
          <div class="step-card reveal">
            <div class="step-num">01 Scope</div>
            <h3>Straight conversation</h3>
            <p>Tell us what's broken or what you're building. We'll tell you what it takes and whether we're the right fit.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="step-card reveal">
            <div class="step-num">02 Build</div>
            <h3>Senior hands on it</h3>
            <p>No juniors, no outsourcing. The work gets done properly, with quality gates and zero shortcuts.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="step-card reveal">
            <div class="step-num">03 Hand over</div>
            <h3>Yours to run</h3>
            <p>Documentation, runbooks, and an operating model. Not a dependency — a platform you own.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <div class="cta-band">
      <div class="container reveal">
        <h2 class="h-display">
          Tell us what's broken.<br />
          <span class="accent">We'll tell you how to fix it.</span>
        </h2>
        <p style="color: var(--muted-d); font-size: var(--fs-2); margin-bottom: 32px;">No pitch. No proposal theatre. Just a direct technical conversation.</p>
        <div class="actions">
          <button class="btn btn-primary" type="button" data-modal-open>
            Get in Touch <span class="arr">›</span>
          </button>
          <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/services">View Services</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

  </div>
</BaseLayout>
